Thanks for assigning this issue to me. I'm starting to work on it and will keep this PR's description up to date as I form a plan and make progress.

Original issue description:

> ### ESLint version
> 
> v9.30.0
> 
> ### What problem do you want to solve?
> 
> This code should be valid
> 
> ```ts
> const myRuleThatUsesDeprecatedButStillPresentAPIs = {
>    create(context: { markVariableAsUsed(name: string): boolean } ) {
>       context.markVariableAsUsed('lol');
>       return {};
>    }
> }
> 
> defineConfig({
>   plugins: {
>     'some-plugin': {
>       rules: {
>         'some-rule': myRuleThatUsesDeprecatedButStillPresentAPIs // <-- TS ERROR
>       }
>     }
>   }
> });
> ```
> 
> note that this _is_ valid:
> 
> ```ts
> import { defineConfig } from 'eslint/config';
> import { Rule } from 'eslint';
> 
> const ruleDefinedUsingESLintType: Rule.RuleModule = {
>   create(
>     context
>   ) {
>     // this call is allowed!
>     context.markVariableAsUsed('lol');
>     return {};
>   }
> }
> 
> defineConfig({
>   plugins: {
>     'some-plugin': {
>       rules: {
>         'some-rule': ruleDefinedUsingESLintType
>       }
>     }
>   }
> })
> ```
> 
> Here is a [TS Playground link](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play/?#code/JYWwDg9gTgLgBAbzgEwKYDNgDtUGEJaYDmcAvnOlBCHAOSoDOANtjAPQDGBxtA3AFChIsRHABKAVyaoyFKjXrNWffvzZs4Ad2gBrBvy5YG8KFNQARDNlTIAqg2xEAogGUAMqwAqATzCoAXOJmAHSS0gCyEMhmcAC8iPxwcBxQqACGMKgAFIlJyQSZAB4wuQCUCXlw6nAwABbADMlpTExwDXDNTBCaNgCEuUmGRTDBIGlQOgBq48BpAEbSAIIM9jZZtF1MtKUClakwElBYiKS7ZPyk-GiYOPiEwERZCLlgTBJE2AyBz5W0DNSoAC0r3e2Fo3wGeVM0i+FUqeT+AMB0NQ4LgKMsNxs9kcrg8WBgPj8kKSl0qZPOpFKqmq-wANDV6o0GLUIFJkB0mP8tLoDARjHAQN4wqhPLUMqsGJYwKkOBkbAAhCQwFwwYAtAAKqQYqAJiw1AElGvEfoNUvKskNUMVvoLxlMZvMlisdcgslg0iAAnBjFBHKVAnMIBBpGljuRyqbKlbiqN7dM-U7UMtVm6NiHtmc9qgDkcTlnLpdrtY7sQni83h8jBDfv8vcDK2Ca-CUbCo-DEfWUWihSKxRKdVLUDLUHLMsglSq1ZrtbqYPqjSTzuTcoXqWoNGL2u06jIJDqmge6hk7TBMlBGuhoDVfIwUsAwDBAYwWAT-PwYLe4OFhWYiTITVyFJ0kyS0CmtGBbTGCYE1mBZkxdNYPS9QJfX9QNg1DcMAxOC4rlHJhxhkQwBV7MxAh-PtbwEYtbm4B5yySEEqzbSFOyBZimzhPYzFY+EETrIFu0CMjpDpJcKVJVcLh2IA) with more demos.
> 
> ### What do you think is the correct solution?
> 
> A rule with a context object that has `markVariableAsUsed(name): string` declared should be able to be assigned to the types used in `defineConfig()`.
> 
> ### Participation
> 
> - [ ] I am willing to submit a pull request for this change.
> 
> ### Additional comments
> 
> This is a blocker for https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/pull/11337


Fixes #19903.

